This is the most analytically defensible engagement ring buy in the entire market. At $3,230 for the stone plus $500–$700 for a quality 4-prong solitaire in 14k white gold, total ring cost is $3,730–$3,930. The 1ct round at 6.5mm delivers full visual presence, GIA certification, and GIA Excellent cut. G color is face-up white. VS2 is eye-clean. There is nothing to improve at this tier without spending significantly more for zero visible gain.

**Why not F-VS2 at $3,490?** The $260 upgrade from G to F is 8% more for a color difference that requires a grading lightbox to detect. The correct choice is G.

**Why not VS1 at $3,300?** The VS1 at $3,300 costs $70 more than the VS2 at $3,230. Both are eye-clean. VS1 is not worth $70 extra.

